==Galician==
===Etymology===
From Old Galician and {{inh|gl|roa-opt|geitar}}, from {{inh|gl|VL.||jectāre, iectāre}}, from {{inh|gl|la|iactāre}}, present active infinitive of {{m|la|iactō}}. Cognate with {{cog|pt|jeitar}}, {{cog|es|echar}}, {{cog|fr|jeter}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gl|/ʃejˈtaɾ/}}
===Verb===
{{gl-verb|xeit|ar}}
# {{lb|gl|pronominal|dated}} to [[lie down]]
#* '''1869''', Domingo Blanco (ed.), ''A poesía popular en Galicia 1745-1885. Recopilación, estudio e edición crítica (vol. I)'', Vigo: Xerais, page 387:
#*: ''Anque che veño do xeito non che veño de '''xeitar''': veño de tomar sardiñas d'alá do medio do mar.''
#*:: ''Although I came from fishing ["xeito"] I've haven't '''been resting''' ["xeitar"]: I've come from catching sardines in the middle of the sea''
#*:: (there's a pun between ''xeitar'', resting, and ''xeito'', throwing, i.e. fishing)
# {{lb|gl|archaic}} to [[expel]]
# {{lb|gl|archaic}} to [[transfer]] a property
====Conjugation====
{{gl-conj-ar|xeit}}
====Related terms====
* {{l|gl|axeitar}}
* {{l|gl|deitar}}
* {{l|gl|enxeitar}}
* {{l|gl|rexeitar}}
* {{l|gl|xeito}}
* {{l|gl|xeitoso}}
===References===
* {{R:gl:DDGM|jeitar}}
* {{R:gl:DDGM|geitar}}
* “[http://sli.uvigo.es/xelmirez/xelmirez.php?pescuda=%5Bgj%5De%5Bijy%5Dt&corpus=xelmirez jeit]” in Xavier Varela Barreiro & Xavier Gómez Guinovart: Corpus Xelmírez - Corpus lingüístico da Galicia medieval. SLI / Grupo TALG / ILG, 2006-2016.
* {{R:gl:TILG}}

