==English==
{{wp}}
===Etymology===
From {{af|en|xeno-|-glossia}}, borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|xénoglossie}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˌziːnəˈɡlɒsi/|/ˌzɛnəˈɡlɒsi/}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}
# [[knowledge|Knowledge]] of a [[language]] one has never [[learn]]ed.
#* {{quote-book
|en
|date=2007-09-01
|title=The Encyclopedia of Religious Phenomena
|first=J. Gordon
|last=Melton
|publisher=Visible Ink
|location=Canton
|section=keyword “xenoglossy”
|isbn=9781578592098
|ol=9470288M
|page=359
|pageurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=n2LTTK5B_OMC&pg=PA359&dq=xenoglossy
|passage=The most well-documented case of '''xenoglossy''', however, concerned Swiss Medium <span style="font-variant:small-caps">Hélène Smith</span> (1861-1929), who falsely claimed to speak the Martian language.
}}
#: {{syn|en|xenoglossia}}
# [[glossolalia|Glossolalia]].
