#: {{cot|en|Joneser|Zillennial}}
#* {{quote-web |en|url=https://www.good.is/articles/generation-xennials |title=Glad to be a Xennial |last=Stankorb |first=Sarah |work=GOOD |date=September 25, 2014|passage=I was born in 1980. According to some sources, this makes me a Gen Xer. According to others, I’m a Millennial. That makes me what then, a '''Xennial'''? I take online quizzes, like Pew Research Center’s “How Millennial Are You?”, and land dead between Gen X and Millennial due to my personal habits, body piercings, and so many more reasons.}}
#* {{quote-web |en|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/what-is-a-xennial-definition-attribution |title=I Made Up ''Xennial'' 3 Years Ago, So Why Is a Professor in Australia Getting All the Credit? |last=Stankorb |first=Sarah |work={{w|Vogue (magazine)|Vogue}} |date=July 6, 2017|passage='''''Xennial''''' is a term that I first used in a 2014 story for ''GOOD'' magazine, following on the heels of writers like Doree Shafrir, who in 2011 called this cusp generation’s pop-cultural misfit status Generation Catalano, after crowdsourcing the ''My So-Called Life''–inspired term from Danielle Nussbaum on Twitter.}}
#* {{quote-web|en|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/2017/11/09/caught-between-millennials-and-generation-x-youre-xennial/848833001/ |title=You're a xennial&nbsp;— if you're caught between Generation X and millennials |last=Adams |first=Dwight |work={{w|Indianapolis Star}} |date=November 10, 2017|passage=But there's this new group, you may know them&nbsp;— that microgeneration sandwiched between&nbsp;— who feel like they don't really belong to either group {{...}} Love it or hate it, there's a newish name for these lost souls: the "'''xennials'''" (pronounced ZEE-knee-als).}}
